title: Celebrate and log quota resets
updated_at: "2026-07-17T17:06:31Z"
---
When a usage quota window resets (session, weekly, monthly — per provider/profile):

1. **Fun notification** — fire a celebratory Plasma notification (woo-hoo!) so the user notices the reset without staring at the widget.
2. **Structured reset log** — record durable details for debugging unexpected resets:
   - timestamp of observed reset
   - what reset (provider, profile, which window/limit: e.g. session 5h vs weekly 7d)
   - expected reset time *before* the reset (from last known `reset_at` / window end)
   - whether it looks **natural** (reset at/near expected time) vs **unexpected** (early/late/surprise)
   - other useful context: previous usage %, new usage after reset, plan tier if known, raw endpoint if helpful

Scope notes: multi-provider (Claude/Codex/Grok/Z.ai/OpenCode); detect reset by comparing successive poll results; avoid spam if multiple windows reset at once (one notification or clear multi-line summary).